Findings: ICD with biventricular pacing lead remains in place. Stable cardiomegaly accompanied by pulmonary vascular congestion and new interstitial edema, superimposed upon chronic areas of linear scar in the mid and lower lungs. Lungs are overinflated, suggestive of COPD. Small pleural effusions are present bilaterally. Bones are diffusely demineralized.
Impression: Congestive heart failure with interstitial edema and small pleural effusions. Hyperinflated lungs, in keeping with known emphysema on prior CT chest of .
